The paper focuses on data structures and algorithms for heaps, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Specifically, it discusses improvements to Fibonacci heaps, which are a type of data structure used in graph algorithms, such as Dijkstra's shortest path algorithm. This could also fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), as graph theory is a subfield of discrete mathematics. The paper also mentions asymptotic worst-case analysis, which is a common topic in cs.AL (Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses implementation details and practical considerations, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
